      "category": "ai",
      "title": "GPT-5.6 used a prompt to close a 30-year gap in convex optimization",
      "url": "https://old.reddit.com/r/math/comments/1uxj3cy/after_openais_cdc_proof_announcement_gpt56_used_a/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48957779",
      "score": 363,
      "comments": 214,
      "author": "mbustamanter",
      "published": "2026-07-18T13:00:52Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Prompting advanced models like GPT-5.6 can resolve long-standing theoretical bottlenecks in convex optimization and numerical algorithm design.",
        "The breakthrough signals a shift from simple syntactic code generation to solving complex, highly structured mathematical and logic problems.",
        "Using LLMs for heuristic discovery challenges traditional hand-crafted optimization methods, accelerating academic research and algorithmic efficiency."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Reviewing AI Code Is Not A Viable Argument",
      "url": "https://softwaremaxims.com/blog/reviewing-ai-code",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/5kgenk",
      "score": 12,
      "comments": 10,
      "author": "Diana",
      "published": "2026-07-18T16:25:19Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Automation bias and cognitive fatigue make manual peer review of LLM-generated code an unreliable defense against subtle security or logical bugs.",
        "Treat LLM output as untrusted third-party code, requiring strict isolation, sandboxing, and rigorous, automated test suites to validate execution safety.",
        "Shift security left by enforcing deterministic CI/CD checks, SAST scanning, and runtime verification instead of relying on human PR approvals."
      ]
    },
